	<h1>Ordering & Purchasing</h1>
	<h2>What payment methods do you accept?</h2>
	<br> We accept Visa and MasterCard on our website. Our sales staff
	can also process other payment types manually, including checks and
	internet banking.
	<br> To pay using one of these methods, please contact us to place
	your order.
	<br>
	<h2>
		Do you offer volume discounts?<br>
	</h2>
	Sorry, we do not offer volume discounts direct to the public.
	<br> For quantity pricing, please contact your local distributor.
	<br>
	<h2>My shipping address is in Texas, but I qualify for a tax
		exemption. Can I buy online?</h2>
	<br> Unfortunately we can't process tax exempt orders through our
	website. But we're happy to process tax exempt orders offline -
	<br>please contact us to place your order and send through your
	Resale Certificate.
	<br>
	<h2>Can I obtain a credit account and use a purchase order to
		shop?</h2>
	<br> We are happy to supply goods on credit. To apply for a credit
	account you will need to fill out the following form and return it to
	us by email (sales@defineinstruments.com) or post it to:
	<br> Define Instruments Inc. 11516 Forest Heights Drive, Dallas,
	TX 75229.
	<br>

	<h1>Delivery</h1>
	<h2>How can I track my shipment?</h2>
	<br> Our staff will be happy to provide you with a tracking number
	to track your parcel.
	<br> Please contact us for your tracking number, and then track it
	on the UPS website.
	<br>
	<h2>When will my In Stock order be dispatched?</h2>
	<br> We stock a comprehensive range of instruments at our Dallas
	office.
	<br> If your item is In Stock, we can usually ship on the same day
	for orders placed before 1pm, and the next day for orders placed after
	1pm.
	<br> Our aim is to get your order on board with the courier within
	two business days of purchase.
